Fog-side politics runs on paperwork and blood. The **Harbormaster’s Office** keeps manifests clean and patrols honest—on paper—while quietly auctioning dock access and “lost” cargo to fund a private intelligence file on everyone who moves through the piers. The **Gullknife Union** claims it protects stevedores from starvation wages, yet skims shipments and runs a disappearance-for-hire pipeline through sealed containers. Across the waterline, the **Saint Brigid Mission** feeds the hungry and shelters runaways, but launders secrets via confession, trading names to buy influence and “save” chosen souls. The Harbormaster leans on the Mission for leads; the Union bleeds both, and all three circle the same missing persons.

```json
{
  "factions": [
    {
      "name": "Harbormaster’s Office",
      "public_front": "Regulates the docks, inspects cargo, assigns berths, and keeps order with official patrols.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Sells access, reroutes ‘lost’ freight, and builds a blackmail-heavy intelligence archive to control the waterfront."
    },
    {
      "name": "Gullknife Union",
      "public_front": "A dockworkers’ union promising protection, fair pay, and safety against exploitative bosses.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Runs smuggling and a disappearance-for-hire operation using sealed containers, forged manifests, and paid muscle."
    },
    {
      "name": "Saint Brigid Mission",
      "public_front": "A charitable mission offering soup, beds, and sanctuary for the desperate and displaced.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Turns confessions into currency, trading names and secrets for leverage while quietly selecting who gets ‘saved’ and who gets sold out."
    }
  ]
}
```

